import { Component } from '@angular/core'; import { Book, BookType } from 'src/app/interfaces/book'; import { BookService } from 'src/app/services/book/book.service'; @Component({ selector: 'app-book', templateUrl: './book.component.html', styleUrls: ['./book.component.scss'] }) export class BookComponent { book: Book= { id: '', name: '', bookType: BookType.ACADEMIC, description: '', price: 0, quantity: 0 }; bookTypeOptions: string[] = Object.values(BookType); constructor(private bookService: BookService) { } createBook() { this.bookService.createBook(this.book).subscribe( response => { console.log('Book created successfully:', response); }, error => { console.error('Error creating book:', error); } ); } }
